{"word":"G3563 - νοῦς - noûs - nooce - Mind","slug":"G3563","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">νοῦς</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>noûs"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>nooce"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Mind"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BD;&#x03BF;&#x03C5;&#x0342;&#x03C2; - nous</b> - <i>nooce</i><p/>Probably from the base of <a href=\"#/G1097\">G1097</a>; the <i>intellect</i>, that is, <i>mind</i> (divine or human; in thought, feeling, or will); by implication <i>meaning</i>: - mind, understanding. Compare <a href=\"#/G5590\">G5590</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3562\">G3562</a>"}]}